In order for men and women to have well-balanced minds, all the powers of the being should be called into use and developed. . . .  {RC 147.10}  
     [The Lord] bids us reason from cause to effect, to remember that we are His property, and to unite with Him in keeping the body pure and healthy, and the whole being sanctified to Him.--Counsels to Parents and Teachers, pp. 295-300.  {RC 147.11}  

Chap. 134 - Appropriate Exercise 

     Whatsoever thy hand findeth to do, do it with thy might; for there is no work, nor device, nor knowledge, nor wisdom, in the grave, whither thou goest. Ecclesiastes 9:10.
